<!-- Button trigger modal -->
<button type="button" class="btn mr-1 px-2 py-1" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#enemiesClearedModal">
<i class="bi bi-question-circle"></i>
</button>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal" id="enemiesClearedModal" tabindex="-1">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h1 class="modal-title fs-5">Enemies cleared during escape</h1>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
      <p>If this option is enabled, enemies do not spawn during the escape.</p>
      
      <p>If this option is disabled, in many rooms enemies will cause heavy lag and visual glitches during the escape (much of which
      is vanilla game behavior but not normally observable in casual play). </p>

      <p>Note that regardless of whether or not this option is enabled, the randomizer opens up barriers during the escape as follows:
      <ul>
      <li>All bosses/minibosses are cleared.
      <li>Shaktool Room is cleared.
      <li>Acid Chozo Statue acid is drained.
      <li>Maridia Tube is broken.
      </ul>
      
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
